<inner> backInCubic(t, b, c, d) → {Number}

Moves back first before easing in.
Parameters:
Name Type Description
t Number Current time passed since the beginning of the animation. Must be >=0. Will be clamped to the duration.
b Number The start value of the property being tweened
c Number The desired delta. E.g. if b = 10, and you want to tween it to 30, c should be 20
d Number The duration in the same units as t.
